.env
.env.*
*.log
nginx/
systemd/
satellite/
# Runtime data dirs created by sibling stacks (monitoring/proxy) — owned by
# the container user (root for grafana, npm), so an unprivileged docker
# build context walk fails with "permission denied" on grafana-data/csv,
# letsencrypt/, etc. None of this belongs in any service image anyway.
monitoring/
proxy/
# scripts/ — DO NOT exclude. The directory contains both host-only shell
# helpers (add-vpn-client.sh, setup-bluetooth-printer.sh, etc.) AND
# container-runnable Python modules (scripts/sync_card_mirror.py and
# scripts/mirror_failure_log.py) that are imported as `scripts.*`.
# Excluding the whole directory broke `python -m scripts.sync_card_mirror`
# inside the sync container with ModuleNotFoundError. The .sh helpers
# are harmless dead weight in the image (~100 KB total); the .py modules
# are required. If you need to keep host-only files out, list them
# individually below instead of excluding the directory.
install.sh
setup-*.sh
README.md
desktop_monitor.py
